# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Index for AI Agents

This file is the canonical entry point for any LLM working in this project.
Generated by layermark-starter; ships with a curated skill set, doctrine
corpus, and category-specific patterns.

When you (an AI agent) start a session, read CLAUDE.md first. This llms.txt
is a faster index for "where to find X" — not a replacement for CLAUDE.md.

## Read these in order at session start

1. CLAUDE.md (project root)
   The canonical project guide. Auto-detected wizard answers, stack, rules,
   risk profile, prompt-engineer mode toggle.

2. 02-memory/decisions-log.md
   Phase 0.7 risk profile + subsequent non-trivial decisions. agent-approval
   skill reads this at runtime as source-of-truth for what mode to apply.

3. 02-memory/category/<NN>-<slug>.md (if exists)
   Category-specific patterns + risk profile + anti-patterns. Auto-loaded
   by Phase 0.3 wizard answer.

## Agents (.claude/agents/)

prompt-engineer.md
  Three-mode doctrine agent. (1) BUILD: casual request → structured prompt.
  (2) AUDIT: doctrine violation finder + always-on security pass. (3)
  PREMORTEM: Kahneman anti-bias plan stress-test (explicit-only trigger).
  Triggers: build, audit, security check, premortem, "X yap", "Y ekle",
  "kontrol et", "bu plan nasıl çöker".

(HIGH-RISK categories only — copied based on Phase 0.3:)

finance-auditor.md (category=finance)
  5 atomic checks: Decimal usage, double-entry, immutable ledger,
  idempotency, transaction boundary.
  Triggers: finance audit, ledger review, decimal precision, money math.

legal-disclaimer-checker.md (category=legal)
  5 atomic checks: disclaimer presence, jurisdiction citation, PII
  handling, regulation citation, no-absolute-claims.
  Triggers: legal review, disclaimer, jurisdiction, PII, KVKK, GDPR.

## Skills (.claude/skills/) — 15 curated

Each passes the inner-loop test (Pocock #9 — rules emerge from friction).
Full decision tree: .claude/skills/README.md.

grill-me
  Reach shared understanding before non-trivial work (one question at a
  time, recommend-first, walk the design tree).
  Triggers: new feature, refactor, design decision, ambiguous request,
  3+ files.

skill-creator
  ASSESS / ADVISE / CREATE for new-skill decisions; operationalizes
  inner-loop test.
  Triggers: same pattern 2-3x/day, should this be a skill.

agent-creator
  3-mode subagent creator (BUILD / AUDIT / SECURITY).
  Triggers: new subagent, long-lived project, multi-agent.

project-advisor
  Monthly audit. HIGH-RISK Step 1.5 (immutable ledger, double-entry,
  jurisdiction citation checks).
  Triggers: end of week/month, drift check, doctrine review.

yardim
  TR/EN troubleshooting; paste error → plain-language explanation +
  fix steps.
  Triggers: error message, what does this mean.

suspend
  Checkpoint current session; emits CONCRETE next step + RESUME PROMPT
  block.
  Triggers: smart-zone limit approaching, fresh window time.

resume
  Loads latest /suspend checkpoint, one-line recap of where you left off.
  Triggers: opened fresh window, picking up.

sync-drift
  Multi-folder drift detection (wiki ↔ raw alignment).
  Triggers: 3-layer KB, raw updated, wiki stale.

ne-yapayim
  Idle-prompt 4-option menu — turns "now what?" into structured route.
  Triggers: stuck, decision fatigue.

spagetti-check
  Tier-1 code-smell (350+ lines, deep nesting, duplication).
  Triggers: refactor question, code complexity hotspot.

ubiquitous-language
  DDD ubiquitous-language; team + Claude shared glossary.
  Triggers: new domain term, no shared meaning.

failing-test-as-prompt
  Test starts red; if green, spec is wrong.
  Triggers: before implementing new feature, TDD.

agent-approval
  Gates significant actions in HIGH-RISK categories. Reads decisions-log.md
  for current risk mode (lokal / sandbox / production).
  Triggers: production action, irreversible move, money-moving.

verify-agent-output
  Doctrine #6 implementation; deterministic pillar of multi-grader rubric
  (independent 2nd path). One-shot manual.
  Triggers: claim/number/result produced, demand evidence.

premortem
  Kahneman anti-bias plan stress-test. Assumes plan ALREADY FAILED 6
  months from now; emits 5-7 failure scenarios with base-rate citation +
  biggest hidden assumption + revised plan diff. Explicit-only trigger.
  Triggers: "premortem", "ölü post-mortem", "bu plan nasıl çöker",
  "stress-test bu kararı".

